Delete truncate AND drop

1 Delete= we use it when we want to delete something with our condition

ex=DELETE FROM Employee
WHERE id = 1;

2 truncate= we use it when we want to delete all data present inside the table but table structure remain same 

ex= Removes all rows from a table.

TRUNCATE TABLE Employee;

Result:

Table Exists
All Rows Removed

3 Drop = if we want to remove all data as wel as table then we use Drop

ex=Removes the entire table.

DROP TABLE Employee;

Result:

Table Deleted
Data Deleted
Structure Deleted

Note = You can rollback a DELETE only if the DELETE is executed inside a transaction and has not been committed yet.
                    STEPES 
ex = 1 START TRANSACTION;

       2 DELETE FROM Employee
WHERE id = 1;

3 ROLLBACK;  The deleted row comes back.

if we commit then we cant rollback 

ex = START TRANSACTION;

DELETE FROM Employee
WHERE id = 1;

COMMIT;

ROLLBACK;  Will not restore the row after the commit.

